<L>__{interior corky's apartment night}
<A>__{it is a hole but it is home. corky is lying on her futon staring up at the ceiling, a beer resting on her stomach; a folk singer quietly croons from the radio. we see the ceiling, a circle of light hovering over the small desk lamp. we move in on the spot, which slowly fills up the screen until there is nothing but the white light. suddenly a wet paint roller loaded with white paint cuts a swath across the ceiling.}
